frus:attachment.p:
Sec. 12.—The Chinese Government agree to open to foreign trade, on the same
                        footing as the places opened to foreign trade by the Treaties of Nanking and
                        Tientsin, the following places namely:— 

Ch’angsha in Hunan;

Wanhsien in Szechuen;

Nganking in Anhui;

Waichow (Hui-chow) in Kuangtung; and

Kongmoon (Chiang-mên)in Kuangtung.
